  "local_port": 48018,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the recipes of five minutes easy to make snacks?",
  "response": "Sure! Here are five easy and delicious snack recipes that you can prepare in just five minutes:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Avocado Toast**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 ripe avocado\n- 2 slices of bread (whole grain, sourdough, etc.)\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- Optional toppings: cherry tomatoes, red pepper flakes, a squeeze of lemon juice, or a drizzle of olive oil\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Toast the Bread:** Start by toasting your bread slices to your desired level of crispiness.\n2. **Prepare the Avocado:** While the bread is toasting, cut the avocado in half, remove the pit, and scoop the flesh into a bowl. Mash it with a fork until smooth or leave it slightly chunky based on your preference.\n3. **Season:** Add salt and pepper to the mashed avocado, and mix in any optional seasonings like a squeeze of lemon juice for extra flavor.\n4. **Assemble:** Spread the mashed avocado evenly onto the toasted bread slices.\n5. **Add Toppings:** Top with your choice of cherry tomatoes, red pepper flakes, or a drizzle of olive oil for added taste and texture.\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Peanut Butter Banana Sandwich**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 2 slices of bread\n- 2 tablespoons peanut butter (or any nut/seed butter)\n- 1 banana\n- Honey (optional)\n- A sprinkle of chia seeds or cinnamon (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Spread Peanut Butter:** Evenly spread peanut butter on one side of each bread slice.\n2. **Add Banana:** Slice the banana and layer the slices on top of the peanut butter on one slice of bread.\n3. **Sweeten (Optional):** Drizzle a little honey over the banana slices and sprinkle with chia seeds or cinnamon for extra flavor.\n4. **Assemble:** Place the second slice of bread on top, peanut butter side down.\n5. **Serve:** Press gently, cut in half if desired, and enjoy!\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Yogurt and Fruit Parfait**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 cup Greek yogurt (or any yogurt of your choice)\n- \u00bd cup granola\n- 1 cup mixed fresh fruits (berries, banana slices, mango, etc.)\n- Honey or maple syrup (optional)\n- A sprinkle of nuts or seeds (optional)\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Layer Yogurt:** Spoon half of the yogurt into a glass or bowl.\n2. **Add Fruits and Granola:** Add a layer of mixed fresh fruits, followed by a layer of granola.\n3. **Repeat Layers:** Add the remaining yogurt on top, then another layer of fruits and granola.\n4. **Sweeten (Optional):** Drizzle honey or maple syrup over the top if desired.\n5. **Garnish:** Sprinkle with nuts or seeds for added crunch and nutrition.\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Caprese Skewers**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 pint cherry tomatoes\n- 8 oz fresh mozzarella balls (bocconcini)\n- Fresh basil leaves\n- Balsamic glaze or balsamic vinegar\n- Salt and pepper, to taste\n- Wooden toothpicks or small skewers\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Assemble Skewers:** On each toothpick or skewer, thread one cherry tomato, one mozzarella ball, and one fresh basil leaf. Repeat until all ingredients are used.\n2. **Season:** Arrange the skewers on a serving plate and sprinkle with salt and pepper.\n3. **Add Balsamic Glaze:** Drizzle balsamic glaze or a few drops of balsamic vinegar over the skewers for a tangy finish.\n4. **Serve:** Enjoy immediately or refrigerate for a quick snack later.\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Microwave Cheese Quesadilla**\n\n**Ingredients:**\n- 1 large flour tortilla\n- \u00bd cup shredded cheese (cheddar, mozzarella, or a blend)\n- Optional fillings: sliced jalape\u00f1os, cooked chicken, black beans, or veggies\n- Salsa or sour cream for dipping\n\n**Instructions:**\n1. **Prepare Quesadilla:** Place the flour tortilla on a microwave-safe plate. Sprinkle shredded cheese evenly over half of the tortilla. Add any optional fillings if desired.\n2. **Fold and Cook:** Fold the tortilla in half to cover the fillings. Microwave on high for 1 minute, or until the cheese is melted.\n3. **Check and Heat More if Needed:** If the cheese isn't fully melted, microwave in additional 15-second intervals until done.\n4. **Serve:** Let it cool for a minute, then cut into wedges using a pizza cutter or knife.\n5. **Dip and Enjoy:** Serve with salsa, sour cream, or your favorite dipping sauce.\n\n---\n\nThese snacks are not only quick to prepare but also versatile, allowing you to customize them based on your preferences and the ingredients you have on hand. Enjoy your snacking!",
